page.title: 16BAGSHOT PARK / UNEMPLOYMENT
page.content:
Many trees like oak and chestnut are in the 360 acres.Forty one trees are preserved specimens, in some cases being{one of the only two known {specimens in the United Kingdom,}the other being in Kew Gardens.
{UNEMPLOYMENT IN CAMBERLEY { On the 9th of May 1985 there was 910 young people registered as unemployed at the careers offices, but it has reduced since May 1984 when they had 998 unemployed. There were 1593 young people wanting to join in with the {youth training scheme (YTS).}On the 14th of April 1985 there were 17 vacancies in Camberley.
